{"data":{"actions":[{"callId":"chatcmpl-tool-ae00538baadeef3d","input":{"filename":"triage_action_report.md","title":"Support Ticket Triage Prioritized Action Report","markdown":"# Support Ticket Triage Prioritized Action Report\n\n**Prepared by:** Support Ticket Triage Agent (ID: 04-support-ticket-triage)\n\n**Date:** 2026-06-18\n\n---\n\n## 1. Evidence Base\n- **Dossier Loaded:** Confirmed agent role, rules, and required evidentiary standards.\n- **Record Analysis (limit 10):**\n  - Total records: 3\n  - Aggregate risk score: 19 (high)\n  - Aggregate opportunity score: 9.1 (moderate)\n  - Top records:\n    1. **04‑A – \"Support ticket triage priority case\"** (status: **urgent**, impact: 43,268, risk score: 12)\n    2. **04‑C – \"Support ticket triage blocked follow‑up\"** (status: **blocked**, impact: 18,844, risk score: 5)\n    3. **04‑B – \"Support ticket triage routine queue item\"** (status: **in_review**, impact: 9,452, risk score: 2)\n\n## 2. Assumptions\n- The risk and opportunity scores provided by `analyze_records` are current and reflect the latest operational state.\n- No additional hidden tickets exist beyond the three records returned (the analysis limit captured all active items).\n- All tickets are self‑contained; no external dependencies beyond what is described in the records.\n- Escalation rules apply: any ticket with potential billing, legal, security, or data‑loss implications must be flagged, though none are explicitly labeled as such in the current records.\n\n## 3. Prioritized Action Plan (under 500 words)\n\n| Priority | Ticket ID | Title | Status | Impact | Risk Score | Recommended Action |\n|----------|----------|-------|--------|--------|------------|--------------------|\n| **1** | 04‑A | Support ticket triage priority case | urgent | 43,268 | 12 | **Immediate response**: Assign dedicated analyst, begin root‑cause investigation, and prepare a mitigation checklist. Escalate to senior support lead. Verify no billing/legal/security flags;